{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850265019,"sessionID":"ses_287143db5ffe4Dmq7fzOXN4MLB","part":{"id":"prt_d78ec1394001lxdMoCo806Sa1q","messageID":"msg_d78ebf697001qY0JBD8txYIqBF","sessionID":"ses_287143db5ffe4Dmq7fzOXN4MLB","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_3ebe3edac3bd4121b74a48a7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义\n\n## Summary\n\nDefine and implement a `Store` interface in `pkg/store` for persisting sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with Redis and Valkey backend support. The interface supports session CRUD operations, expiry and last-activity indexing for garbage collection, and provider selection via configuration.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe agentcube system requires persistent storage for sandbox metadata associated with user sessions. Currently, there is no standardized interface for session storage, making it difficult to:\n- Support different storage backends (Redis, Valkey)\n- Index sessions for garbage collection (expired/inactive sessions)\n- Maintain session metadata independently of the runtime lifecycle\n\n### Goal\n\nImplement a `Store` interface with:\n- Unified API for session CRUD operations\n- Support for Redis and Valkey backends\n- Indexed queries for expired and inactive sessions\n- Singleton access pattern for application-wide storage\n\n### Value\n- Backend flexibility: Choose Redis or Valkey based on deployment requirements\n- Efficient garbage collection: Query sessions by expiry or activity time\n- Clean separation: Storage logic isolated from business logic\n- Kubernetes integration: Leverages client-go patterns from AR-010\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| Store Interface | Define `Store` interface with all CRUD and listing methods |\n| Redis Implementation | Implement `redisStore` with Redis client (go-redis/v9) |\n| Valkey Implementation | Implement `valkeyStore` with Valkey client (valkey-go) |\n| Singleton Access | Provide `Storage()` function with sync.Once initialization |\n| Index Maintenance | Maintain ZSET indexes for expiry and last_activity |\n| Error Handling | Return `ErrNotFound` for missing sessions |\n\n### Code Structure\n\n```\npkg/store/\n├── store.go                    # Store interface definition\n├── singleton.go                # Singleton Storage() and initStore()\n├── errors.go                   # ErrNotFound definition\n├── types.go                    # Constants for store types\n├── store_redis.go              # Redis implementation\n├── store_valkey.go             # Valkey implementation\n└── (generated test files...)\n```\n\n### Configuration\n\n| Variable | Type | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| STORE_TYPE | string | No | \"redis\" | Storage provider (redis/valkey) |\n| REDIS_ADDR | string | If redis | - | Redis server address |\n| REDIS_PASSWORD | string | If redis* | - | Redis password |\n| REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED | string | No | true | Set to \"false\" to allow empty password |\n| VALKEY_ADDR | string | If valkey | - | Valkey server addresses (comma-separated) |\n| VALKEY_PASSWORD | string | If valkey* | - | Valkey password |\n| VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED | string | No | true | Set to \"false\" to allow empty password |\n| VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE | string | No | false | Set to \"true\" to disable cache |\n| VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE | string | No | false | Set to \"true\" to force single client |\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n- Session replication across clusters — future enhancement\n- Session data encryption at rest — future enhancement\n- Connection pooling configuration — future enhancement\n- Metrics and observability — future enhancement (AR-013)\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n|------------|--------|---------|\n| github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 | ^9.x | Redis client |\n| github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go | latest | Valkey client |\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types | local | SandboxInfo type |\n| k8s.io/klog/v2 | ^2.x | Logging (Valkey options) |\n\n### Upstream Dependencies\n\n- **AR-010 Session Management** — Consumes Store for session CRUD\n- **AR-009 Router Core** — May use Store for session context\n- **pkg/common/types** — Provides `SandboxInfo` struct\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Session Manager** — Creates, reads, updates, deletes sessions\n2. **Garbage Collector** — Queries expired/inactive sessions for cleanup\n3. **Health Checks** — Uses Ping to verify backend connectivity\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Backend unavailability | High | Health checks, graceful degradation |\n| Key conflicts | Medium | Use namespaced key prefixes |\n| Data inconsistency | Medium | Use pipeline/multi for atomic operations |\n| Password in env | Medium | Require explicit opt-in for empty passwords |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Redis + Valkey via Factory (Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Single `Store` interface with factory function selecting implementation based on `STORE_TYPE`.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Simple API: callers use `Storage()` without knowing backend\n- Easy to add new backends (in-memory, etcd, etc)\n- Consistent interface across implementations\n- Matches Kubernetes client patterns\n\n**Cons**:\n- Slight runtime dispatch overhead\n- More complex testing (mock interface required)\n\n**Decision**: Selected — provides flexibility and clean abstraction.\n\n---\n\n### Option 2: Separate Interfaces per Backend\n\n**Approach**: Define `RedisStore` and `ValkeyStore` interfaces separately.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Type-safe backend selection at compile time\n- No runtime dispatch\n\n**Cons**:\n- Duplicated method signatures\n- Callers must know backend type\n- Difficult to swap backends without code changes\n\n**Decision**: Rejected — less flexible, harder to maintain.\n\n---\n\n### Option 3: Generic Key-Value Store\n\n**Approach**: Use generic KV interface (Get, Set, Delete) and build session logic on top.\n\n**Pros**:\n- More general purpose\n- Can reuse for other data\n\n**Cons**:\n- Loses session-specific semantics (expiry index, activity tracking)\n- Requires more code in consumers to handle session lifecycle\n\n**Decision**: Rejected — session-specific operations are core to the use case.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Interface and Types\n- [ ] Define `Store` interface with all methods\n- [ ] Define `ErrNotFound` error\n- [ ] Define store type constants\n- [ ] Define `SandboxInfo` and `SandboxEntryPoint` types (or import from pkg/common/types)\n\n### Phase 2: Redis Implementation\n- [ ] Implement `redisStore` struct\n- [ ] Implement `makeRedisOptions` for connection config\n- [ ] Implement all Store methods for Redis\n- [ ] Use pipeline for atomic multi-command operations\n- [ ] Handle ZSET operations for expiry and last_activity indexes\n\n### Phase 3: Valkey Implementation\n- [ ] Implement `valkeyStore` struct\n- [ ] Implement `makeValkeyOptions` for connection config\n- [ ] Implement all Store methods for Valkey\n- [ ] Use DoMulti for atomic operations\n- [ ] Handle optional DisableCache and ForceSingleClient\n\n### Phase 4: Singleton and Initialization\n- [ ] Implement `Storage()` with sync.Once\n- [ ] Implement `initStore()` with provider selection\n- [ ] Handle environment variable parsing\n- [ ] Add password required validation\n- [ ] Log fatal on initialization failure\n\n### Phase 5: Testing\n- [ ] Unit tests for interface methods\n- [ ] Unit tests for key construction\n- [ ] Unit tests for error handling (not found, validation)\n- [ ] Integration tests with Redis/Valkey (if available)\n- [ ] Fake implementations for client testing\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `Store` interface is defined in `pkg/store`\n- [ ] `Storage()` returns initialized store singleton\n- [ ] Redis backend implements all Store methods\n- [ ] Valkey backend implements all Store methods\n- [ ] `STORE_TYPE` selects correct backend\n- [ ] Missing session returns `ErrNotFound`\n- [ ] Session key uses `session:{id}` format\n- [ ] Expiry index maintained in `session:expiry` ZSET\n- [ ] Last-activity index maintained in `session:last_activity` ZSET\n- [ ] `ListExpiredSandboxes` queries by expiry time\n- [ ] `ListInactiveSandboxes` queries by last activity\n- [ ] `StoreSandbox` uses atomic pipeline/multi\n- [ ] `UpdateSandbox` requires existing key (XX flag)\n- [ ] `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` removes from all indexes\n- [ ] `UpdateSessionLastActivity` validates key exists\n- [ ] Password required unless `*_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n- [ ] Invalid STORE_TYPE fails initialization\n- [ ] Unit tests cover core functionality","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775850264979,"end":1775850265016}}}}
